import re
CASES = [('snake', re.compile('\\A[a-z]+(_[a-z]+)+\\Z')), ('kebab', re.compile('\\A[a-z]+(-[a-z]+)+\\Z')), ('camel', re.compile('\\A[a-z]+([A-Z][a-z]*)+\\Z')), ('none', re.compile(''))]

def identify_case(c_str):
    """
    Identifies the case type of the input string.

    Parameters:
    c_str (str): The input string to identify the case type of.

    Returns:
    str: The case type of the input string ('kebab', 'camel', 'snake') or 'none' if the case cannot be identified.
    """
    for (case, pattern) in CASES:
        if pattern.match(c_str):
            return case
    return ''
